  Scenario: Ordering is well defined across all types, ascending
    Given an empty graph
    And having executed:
      """
      CREATE (:A)-[:T]->()
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      MATCH p = (n)-[r]->()
      WITH [n, r, p, '', 1, 3.14, true, null, [], {}] AS types
      UNWIND types AS t
      RETURN t
        ORDER BY t ASC
      """
    Then the result should be, in order:
      | t               |
      | {}              |
      | (:A)            |
      | [:T]            |
      | []              |
      | <(:A)-[:T]->()> |
      | ''              |
      | true            |
      | 1               |
      | 3.14            |
      | null            |
    And no side effects

